# English only

All project content must be in English (United States).

## Requirements

- User-facing UI copy: labels, headings, buttons, placeholders, tooltips, empty states, and error messages — English only.
- Code comments and documentation — English only.
- Do not add Hindi or other non-English strings to source files.
- Use `APP_LOCALE` (`en-US`) from `src/utils/locale.js` for dates and numbers instead of `en-IN` or browser-default locales.
- Prefer clear, plain business English over jargon or AI-sounding filler (e.g. avoid "execution rails", "operating cadence", "instrumented via").

## Formatting

- Dates: `formatAppDate()` / `formatAppDateTime()` from `src/utils/locale.js`
- Numbers: `formatAppNumber()` from `src/utils/locale.js`
